items.maintenance:
1. Drain potable water system (AMM  12-14-01/301).
2. Establish procedures to ensure the potable water system is not serviced.  as below
PLACARD
-For deactivated  or isolated  components,as appropriate-INOP-DONOTUSE. -For inoperative potable water system, Water Service Panel - POTABLE WATER SYS INOP - DO NOTFILL
OPERATIONS NOTE
The aircraft will not normally be dispatched for flights over approximately 1 hour of flight time.
Every possible effort should be made not to dispatch the aircraft from Base or from a station that repairs can be made. NCC shall coordinate with Catering to load adequate bottled water and hand sanitisers, as needed.
3  The Commander, in coordination with NCC, will determine if the flight duration is acceptable taking into consideration:
• the passenger loads;
• the flight time;
• the service level (e.g. Business class passengers, etc.);
• any expected delays;
• any relevant information (e.g. the amount of bottled water available, etc.);
Additionally, the Commander shall inform the Cabin Crew that:
• potable water will not be available throughout the flight;
• the water faucets in galleys and lavatories will be inoperative;
• the toilet flush will still be operative but there will be no water coming out during the flush phase
sequence.
• ensure that adequate bottled water and hand sanitizer is available for the duration of the flight;
• inform passengers in Arabic, English and any other language, as deemed appropriate about the
unserviceability;
• check on a regular basis during the flight that the toilets, if used, are free of waste;
If the lavatories are not to be used, must be secured closed and placarded INOPERATIVE – DO NOT ENTER. Note
: This provision is not intended to prohibit inspections by Crew Members.
